% @category: Getting Started
% @name: Quick Primer
% @description: What's Hyades and how to use it
@cassilda: overview
      ✩                         _  _              _                                ✩
      ✩                        | || |_  _ __ _ __| |___ ___                        ✩
      ✩                        | __ | || / _` / _` / -_(_-<                        ✩
      ✩                        |_||_|\_, \__,_\__,_\___/__/                        ✩
      ✩                                |_/ A Quick Overview                        ✩
      ✩  /....................................................................../  ✩
      ✩                                                                            ✩
      ✩  First of all,  whether you’ve made it to this  notebook because you need  ✩
      ✩  to include pretty math in your code  comments/documentation, or you want  ✩
      ✩  to send it via e-mail and don’t want to install a 5GB TeX  distribution,  ✩
      ✩  or send PDFs/screenshots, thank you for showing interest in 𝐻𝑦𝑎δες.       ✩
      ✩                                                                            ✩
      ✩                                                                            ✩
      ✩                               What Is This?                                ✩
      ✩                               ─────────────                                ✩
      ✩                                                                            ✩
      ✩  A lightweight  CLI program that allows you to render TeX into multi-line  ✩
      ✩  text, and much more!                                                      ✩
      ✩                                                                            ✩
      ✩                    (𝑛)       𝑛!    ⌠       𝑓(𝑧)                            ✩
      ✩                   𝑓   (𝑎) = ─────  ⌽  ──────────────  𝑑𝑧                   ✩
      ✩                              2π𝑖   ⌡          𝑛 + 1                        ✩
      ✩                                    γ   (𝑧 − 𝑎)                             ✩
      ✩                                                                            ✩
      ✩  This ↑ is what you’ll get on the  standard output if you pipe this piece  ✩
      ✩  of LaTeX math into hyades:                                                ✩
      ✩                                                                            ✩
      ✩    $$ f^{(n)}(a) = \frac{n!}{2\pi i}                                       ✩
      ✩       \oint_\gamma \frac{f(z)}{(z-a)^{n+1}} \, dz $$                       ✩
      ✩                                                                            ✩
      ✩  Moreover, you can have it automatically  rendered to your source code as  ✩
      ✩  a comment using  Cassilda (yes,  you’ve correctly  recognized the cosmic  ✩
      ✩  horror  references). We have a VSCode  extension,  and an installer  for  ✩
      ✩  Helix and Neovim!                                                         ✩
      ✩                                                                            ✩
      ✩             ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────┐              ✩
      ✩             │         — 𝑊ℎ𝑎𝑡 𝑖𝑓 𝐼 𝑑𝑜𝑛‘𝑡 𝑘𝑛𝑜𝑤 𝑇𝑒𝑋? —         │              ✩
      ✩             │                                               │              ✩
      ✩             │ 𝐻𝑦𝑎δες has both an online MCP  server, and an │              ✩
      ✩             │ offline  MCP  binary.  You can add  either to │              ✩
      ✩             │ your AI, which will equip it with the  𝐻𝑦𝑎δες │              ✩
      ✩             │ 𝑟𝑒𝑛𝑑𝑒𝑟 tool.                                  │              ✩
      ✩             │                                               │              ✩
      ✩             │  ╔════════════════════════════════════════╗   │              ✩
      ✩             │  ║ https://hyades-mcp.apg.workers.dev/mcp ║   │              ✩
      ✩             │  ╚════════════════════════════════════════╝   │              ✩
      ✩             │                                               │              ✩
      ✩             │ You can  then tell it to write  the math  for │              ✩
      ✩             │ you, e.g.: 𝑈𝑠𝑒 𝐻𝑦𝑎𝑑𝑒𝑠 𝑡𝑜 𝑤𝑟𝑖𝑡𝑒 𝑎 𝑝𝑟𝑜𝑜𝑓 𝑜𝑓 𝑡ℎ𝑒 │              ✩
      ✩             │ 𝐺𝑎𝑢𝑠𝑠𝑖𝑎𝑛 𝐼𝑛𝑡𝑒𝑔𝑟𝑎𝑙                             │              ✩
      ✩             │                                               │              ✩
      ✩             │                    — or —                     │              ✩
      ✩             │                                               │              ✩
      ✩             │ 𝐶𝑜𝑢𝑙𝑑  𝑦𝑜𝑢  𝑢𝑠𝑒  𝐻𝑦𝑎𝑑𝑒𝑠 𝑡𝑜 𝑑𝑒𝑠𝑐𝑟𝑖𝑏𝑒  𝑡ℎ𝑒 𝑚𝑎𝑡ℎ │              ✩
      ✩             │ 𝑡ℎ𝑖𝑠 𝑐𝑜𝑑𝑒  𝑝𝑒𝑟𝑓𝑜𝑟𝑚𝑠, 𝑎𝑛𝑑 𝑎𝑡𝑡𝑎𝑐ℎ 𝑖𝑡 𝑎𝑠 𝑑𝑜𝑐𝑢𝑚𝑒- │              ✩
      ✩             │ 𝑛𝑡𝑎𝑡𝑖𝑜𝑛 ℎ𝑒𝑎𝑑𝑒𝑟𝑠?                              │              ✩
      ✩             └───────────────────────────────────────────────┘              ✩
      ✩                                                                            ✩
      ✩  The rest of this primer will take you through the basic setup and usage,  ✩
      ✩  and if you’ve not had enough by the end of it, there are  follow-up gui-  ✩
      ✩  des with in-depth focus on specific areas.                                ✩
